name: Test -> Control modules 2–8 cabling sequence,
description: Sequentially, for each control module from 2 to 8, open its inspection panel and use a low‑voltage continuity tester (with the battery temporarily removed) to determine which two terminals are bridged by that module’s switch, thereby identifying its internal through‑line pair. Then, with the battery reinserted and all switches ON, use a voltmeter referenced to the PSU negative to verify that the PSU positive is present on the correct through‑line pair at the input and output of each module. Record the first module in the chain where the 12 V continuity or presence is lost or appears on the wrong pair; do not re‑wire anything yet., outcome="Control Switches 2–8 all show nominal continuity (≈0.01 Ω).  \n12 V is present on the positive input and output cables through Control Cube 5; at Control Cube 6, 12 V is present on the positive input but 0 V is measured on the positive output and on all subsequent modules (6–8), and the first noted anomaly is a disconnected end on 'Control Input Cable (+) 6' (port 'n' floating).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=525.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
